11. Rd1 Ba6 {This position has occurred in over 50 games. Most of those games continued with either 12.Bf4 or 12.d5 . Those are good moves, but I wanted to suggest another approach in this course.}
12. Be3 Ν {[%cal Gf3e1,Gf2f4,Gg3g4,Gg4g5,Gf4f5]} {I have two fresh ideas here. Which one is mainline in this course is arbitrary as I like both moves equally well. The alternative 12.Ne1 is covered<a class="commentMoveSmall" href="/variation/18593092/#/12/w" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-tippy-content="Link to variation">here.</a> Actually also after 12.Be3 the knight can still go to e1. The idea is to play f2-f4 and, after some preparation, g3-g4-g5 or f4-f5.} Bb4
13. Ne1 $5 {[%cal Ge1c2,Gc2b4,Gc2e3,Gf2f4]} {Once again the knight is coming to c2, from where it is attacking the bishop on b4 and can come to e3 later. Also, it enables White to push f2-f4.} Qc7 {[%cal Ge6e5]}
