15. Nc2 {[%cal Gc2b4]} Rfd8 {However, the waiting approach is very dangerous for Black.}
16. e5 $5 {16.g4!? is another good way to proceed and might be even more to your liking.} Nd5 {Now White has a rather surprising idea.}
17. Bxd5 cxd5 {Obviously, 17...exd5 18.f5 is very dangerous too. White will play Rf1 next and the e6-push is always in the air.}
18. f5 {[%cal Gd1f1,Ge2g4]} {Next, White brings the heavy pieces over to the kingside. The engines still think Black is ok here but it definitely looks dangerous!}


