13. Qg4 $1 {As usual, this is a key move in our attacking plan. Black now either has to weaken the kingside with ...g6, or give up the right to castle with ...Kf8, which is less weakening, but also Black's rook on h8 will not be participating in the game for a while.} g6 {13...Kf8 14.b3 cxb3 15.axb3 a5 16.h4}
14. b3 cxb3
15. axb3 a5 {Black tries to get some counterplay going on. Potentially, Black has a dangerous passed pawn on the a-file, although, with so many pieces still on the board, we shouldn't worry too much. 15...h5 16.Qf3 O-O 17.Nxd5 cxd5 18.Nf6+ Nxf6 19.exf6 Bd6 20.g4!}
16. Nxd5 $5 {White changes the structure and collects the dark-squared bishop. White will be two pawns down, but with a long-lasting initiative in return for it.} cxd5
