15. Nxd5 cxd5 {This structure is quite common in the closed Catalan. There are some similarities with the French, but compared to that opening, Black finds it very hard to get counterplay on the queenside as Black's pieces are rather passive and the pawn on b6 stopped Black from putting pressure with ...Qb6.}
16. Qd3 {16.Qa4 is the move I <a class="commentMoveSmall" href="/variation/18592996/#/13/w" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-tippy-content="Link to variation">recommend</a> in the course, but it doesn't change the character of the position all that much.} Qc8 {[%cal Gb7a6]}
